        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 10 at 3:28PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 328 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Hapeville, or near
Atlanta, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Atlanta, Decatur, City of South Fulton, East Point, Stockbridge,
Forest Park, Riverdale, College Park, Clarkston, Morrow, Hapeville,
Stone Mountain, Avondale Estates, Lake City, Pine Lake, Tucker,
Belvedere Park, North Decatur, Hartsfield-Jackson Airport, and North
Druid Hills.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
